C({"name": "jQuery.Model.static.findOne", "type": "function", "parent": "jQuery.Model.static", "comment": "<p>FindOne is used to retrive a model instances from the server. By implementing \nfindOne along with the rest of the [jquery.model.services service api], your models provide an abstract\nservice API.</p>\n\n<p>You can implement findOne with a string:</p>\n\n<pre><code>$.Model(\"Thing\",{\n  findOne : \"/things/{id}.json\"\n},{})\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>Or you can implement it yourself. </p>\n\n<pre><code>$.Model(\"Thing\",{\n  findOne : function(params, success, error){\n    var self = this,\n        id = params.id;\n    delete params.id;\n    return $.get(\"/things/\"+id+\".json\",\n      params,\n      success,\n      \"json thing.model\")\n  }\n},{})\n</code></pre>\n\n<h2>API</h2>", "params": {"params": {"order": 0, "description": "<p>data to refine the results. This is often something like {id: 5}.</p>", "name": "params", "type": "Object", "optional": false}, "success(item)": {"order": 1, "description": "<p>called with a model instance</p>", "name": "success(item)", "type": "Function", "optional": false}, "error": {"order": 2, "description": "", "name": "error", "type": "Function", "optional": false}}, "children": []})